  <description type="morphology">Stems commonly unbranched.  Leaf base distinctly and rather abruptly wider than the limb.  Sexual condition dioicous.  Seta 0.8–1.2 cm.  Capsule with theca usually 2–2.8 mm, operculum 0.6–1 mm, peristome not or slightly twisted.</description>
